Lucius E. Burch III: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 3:11 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Massey Burch Capital Corp.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Lucius E. Burch IIIChief Executive Officer and Chairman, Massey Burch Capital Corp.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships75--
Background

		Mr. Lucius E. Burch, III, has been the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Burch Investment Group since October 1989 and is its Partner. Mr. Burch serves as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Massey Burch Capital Corp. He serves as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Collateral Guaranty, a credit enhancement fund. Mr. Burch joined Massey Burch Investment Group (now known as Massey Investment Company) as an Associate, Financial Analyst and Portfolio ... Manager in 1968 and served as its President from 1981 until 1989. His experience in the venture capital industry includes three years at Prudential-Bache Capital Funding as an Analyst in the corporate finance health care group. Mr. Burch served as Commercial Banker of Morgan Guaranty Trust Co., where he began his career. He has extensive experience in management consulting, corporate finance and mergers and acquisitions. Mr. Burch served as the Chairman of Corrections Corporation from January 1999 to 2000. He serves as a Director of Capital Management, Innovative Solutions in Healthcare and United Asset Coverage, Inc. Mr. Burch serves as a Director of QMS, Inc. and Titan Holdings, Inc. He has been a Director of Norrell Corporation since 1982. Mr. Burch served as a Director of MCT Corp. since June 1999. He has been an Independent Director of AAC Holdings, Inc. since February 2012. Mr. Burch serves as a Director at Covenant Surgical Partners, Inc. and BreatheAmerica, Inc. He served as an Independent Director of Corrections Corporation of America from December 2000 to February 2010. Mr. Burch served as a Director of Physicians Resource Group, Inc. He served as a Director of Affirmative Insurance Holdings Inc. until November 8, 2005 and Old CCA since May 1998. Mr. Burch served as a Director of Charisma Communications Corporation. He has served on a number of public and private company boards, including seven NYSE companies. Mr. Burch serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Iroquois Capital Group, Inc. He is awarded with The William Richardson Davie Award. Mr. Burch graduated from the University of North Carolina, where he received a B.A. degree in 1963.Read Full Background




