The Lucius E. Burch III River Center
at the Cumberland River Compact

Resting on the East Bank of the Cumberland River and adjacent to the John Seigenthaler Pedestrian Bridge, The River Center at the Cumberland River Compact boasts one of the most spectacular views of downtown Nashville’s skyline. Located on the third floor of the LEED Platinum Bridge Building, the River Center offers green amenities, a versatile event space, and the serenity of the Cumberland which separates you and your guests from the bustling city while being a short walk from the heart of Nashville.





For Information
For more information about the River Center,  please contact Eleanor Barbee by phone at 615-837-1151 or via email at eleanor.barbee@cumberlandrivercompact.org.
History of the Bridge Building – Read More
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 






















Microsoft personalized ad preferences




 













To opt out of personalized ads in this browser, your browser history must allow first-party and third-party cookies and you must have your browsing experience set to NOT delete browsing history on exit. Instructions for enabling cookies and configuring your browsing history may be available in your browsers settings, privacy, or help documentation.

















